  "prompt": "Who are the best angel investors of all time?",
  "response": "Identifying the \"best\" angel investors of all time can be subjective, as it depends on various factors such as investment success, impact on startups, mentorship, and personal style. However, a few angel investors are often recognized for their significant contributions to the startup ecosystem:\n\n1. **Ron Conway**: Often referred to as the \"Godfather of Silicon Valley,\" Conway has invested in numerous successful companies, including Google, Facebook, and Twitter. His early involvement and networking have made a considerable impact on the tech landscape.\n\n2. **Jeff Clavier**: Founder of SoftTech VC, Clavier has backed many successful startups, including Fitbit and Eventbrite, through his angel investments. He is known for his ability to identify promising early-stage companies.\n\n3. **Naval Ravikant**: Co-founder of AngelList, Ravikant is an influential figure in the tech community. He has invested in over 100 companies, including Twitter, Uber, and Postmates, and is known for his insights on startups and investing.\n\n4. **David Cohen**: Co-founder of Techstars, Cohen has not only invested in numerous startups but has also helped mentor and grow them through the accelerator program.\n\n5. **Aydin Senkut**: Founder of Felicis Ventures, Senkut has made early investments in companies such as Shopify and Fitbit. He has a reputation for picking the right startups to back.\n\n6. **Marlon Nichols**: Co-founder of Cross Culture Ventures, Nichols focuses on diverse founders and has invested in successful companies like Viacom and the podcasting platform, Anchor.\n\n7. **Chris Sacca**: A former Google executive, Sacca has made successful early-stage investments in Twitter, Uber, and Instagram through his investment firm, Lowercase Capital.\n\n8. **Peter Thiel**: Co-founder of PayPal and an early investor in Facebook, Thiel is known for his strategic investments and insights into technology trends.\n\n9. **Angel Investors on AngelList**: Various investors on platforms like AngelList have gained recognition for their successful investments and contributions to early-stage funding.\n\nThese individuals have made substantial contributions to the ecosystem through their investments, mentoring, and support of emerging entrepreneurs. Their ability to recognize potential in startups has led to numerous success stories in the tech industry and beyond.",
